==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tote
<hw>Tote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Toted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Toting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Said to be of African
origin.]</ety> <def>To carry or bear; <as>as, to <ex>tote</ex> a child
over a stream; to <ex>tote</ex> a gun on one's hip</as>; -- a colloquial
word originating in the Southern States, and used there esp. by negroes,
now common throughout the U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tote
<hw>Tote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>totum</ets>, fr.
<ets>totus</ets> all, whole.]</ety> <def>The entire body, or all;
<as>as, the whole <ex>tote</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Totear</ent>⟦br⟧
